 Updates the in-game username for the authenticated user.
 
+Requires `X-CSRF-TOKEN` to match the `csrf_access_token` cookie.
+
 ### 10) `POST /refresh`
 Refreshes access token using refresh token cookie + refresh CSRF token.
 
+Requires `X-CSRF-TOKEN` to match the `csrf_refresh_token` cookie.
+
 ### 11) `POST /logout`
 Clears auth and CSRF cookies.
 
+Requires `X-CSRF-TOKEN` to match the `csrf_access_token` cookie.
+
+## CSRF Contract
+
+All state-changing auth endpoints require a double-submit CSRF token:
+
+- Anonymous endpoints (`POST /register`, `POST /login`) use the `anon_csrf` cookie from `GET /csrf-token`.
+- Authenticated access-token endpoints (`POST /google/link/start`, `POST /google/unlink`, `PATCH /me/username`, `POST /logout`) use the readable `csrf_access_token` cookie.
+- Refresh uses the readable `csrf_refresh_token` cookie.
+- Clients send the selected token in the `X-CSRF-TOKEN` header.
+
+Missing CSRF header/cookie pairs return `401` with `detail: "Missing CSRF token"`.
+Mismatched CSRF header/cookie pairs return `401` with `detail: "CSRF token mismatch"`.
+Invalid, expired, missing, or wrong-type JWT cookies continue to return `401` with `detail: "Invalid or expired token"`.
+
+`GET /me` is read-only but also requires the access CSRF header/cookie pair as part of the authenticated session check.
+
